description:
In order to create some commands
  As a developer
  I want to use jarvis API
name: Mixed cruds

steps.name: I erase all 'device' with 'name' starting with 'mixed'
I erase all 'plugin' with 'name' starting with 'mixed'
I erase all 'command' with 'name' starting with 'mixed'
I create a 'device' with body '{"name":"mixed device", "icon": "save"}' and store it to 'created'
I create a 'plugin' with body '{"name":"mixed plugin", "icon": "drop"}' and store it to 'created'
I create a 'command' with body '{"name":"mixed command", "icon": "save", "body": "return 100;", "type": "LUA"}' and store it to 'created'
I search a 'device' with 'name' equals to 'mixed device' and store it to 'dev001'
the store 'dev001'.'name' must be 'mixed device'
the store 'dev001'.'icon' must be 'save'
I search a 'plugin' with 'name' equals to 'mixed plugin' and store it to 'plug001'
the store 'plug001'.'name' must be 'mixed plugin'
the store 'plug001'.'icon' must be 'drop'
I search a 'command' with 'name' equals to 'mixed command' and store it to 'cmd001'
the store 'cmd001'.'name' must be 'mixed command'
the store 'cmd001'.'type' must be 'LUA'
count 'device' with 'name' equals to 'mixed device' is 1
count 'plugin' with 'name' equals to 'mixed plugin' is 1
count 'command' with 'name' equals to 'mixed command' is 1
I apply 'execute' on 'command' identified by 'cmd001'.'id' and store result to 'exc'
the store 'exc'.'object.result' must be '100'
I link 'device' with name 'mixed device' to 'plugin' with name 'mixed plugin'
I link 'plugin' with name 'mixed plugin' to 'command' with name 'mixed command'
